    \forall\, t \in \mathbb{R} \; \forall\,x\in\mathbb{R}\setminus\{0\}      \qquad : \qquad      \left\vert \frac{\exp(\mathbb{i} tx)-1}{x} \right\vert \leq \vert t\vert 
    \forall\, t\in\mathbb{R} \; \forall\, z\in\mathbb{C}\setminus\{0\}     \qquad : \qquad    \left\vert \frac{\exp(\mathbb{i} tz)-1}{z} \right\vert \leq \vert t \vert 
 |f(t) - f(0)|= \left|\int_0^t f'(u) du\right| \le \int_0^t \left|f'(u)\right| du \le  |t| \sup |f'| 
 f'(t) = ix \exp itx;\\ \sup |f'| = |x|. 
